        <div class="bg-white p-3 rounded mb-3">
            <p>Steve, you mentioned that when an inspection is 100% effective, only one inspection is needed within the PF. However, the challenge lies in accessing the PF in the first place, as the starting point (P point) is usually unpredictable. If the P point is known, the F point can typically be estimated. To guarantee entry into the PF interval, it has been demonstrated that inspecting at 50% or less of the PF interval always ensures entry. This principle can be likened to a common old wives' tale, showcasing the importance of strategic inspection methods.</p>
